# React Conventions

- Build components as pure functions from props and state.
- Do not use inline styles in JSX (`style={{ ... }}`); use style files/modules.
- Keep component files focused; extract hooks/utilities when logic grows.
- Use descriptive prop names and typed props for all exported components.
- Keep JSX readable by avoiding deeply nested conditional expressions.
- Prefer derived values with memoization only when profiling indicates need.
- Ensure accessible semantics for interactive UI (buttons, labels, alt text).
